Hey Ken

No the splash pan doesn't get it the way.   I am saying you NEED the splash
pan. gotta have it
Otherwise the weight of the poles/canvas tilts the bumepr end down.   I saw a
pic of that, and it looked kinda silly.
Just in case your bumper was incomplete, might want to sort it out.

FWIW Greg installed tent mounts last week on my 66 kombi:
http://www.thesamba.com/vw/forum/album_search.php?search_keywords=west*+and+t
ent+and+install*&search_terms=all&search_author=&search_forum%5B%5D=-1&search
_time=0&search_fields=all&show_results=posts&sort_by=0&sort_dir=DESC

If you install the roof mounts slightly too close together it is fine, but if
they are too far apart it will be a problem to install the pole that fits
along the side of the bus there.
more useful tent bumper mount pics:
 http://www.thesamba.com/vw/forum/album_search.php?search_keywords=bumper+and
+tent&search_terms=all&search_author=&search_forum%5B%5D=-1&search_time=0&sea
rch_fields=all&show_results=posts&sort_by=0&sort_dir=DESC

I have drilled a few rear bumpers to make it possible to hang a tent.   :)

