Yes, the poles have been re-popped by I think it was BBT.  The repro poles can
be used with a original awning.  I don't believe they include the spears for
the privey section of the tent.
Does your 67 have the mounts on the roof and front bumper?
The green/white 65 westy I have did have the roof & bumper mounts for the
striped tent, but it seems only the German delivered SO-42s did.
 Most SO-42s came with the big top tent that attaches to the rain gutter.

http://www.thesamba.com/vw/forum/album_page.php?pic_id=292440
http://www.thesamba.com/vw/forum/album_page.php?pic_id=291391
http://www.thesamba.com/vw/forum/album_page.php?pic_id=368836

You do really want to have a splash pan in the rear bumper on the passenger
side before setting up he side tent.
erecting a tent:
http://www.thesamba.com/vw/forum/album_search.php?search_keywords=erect*+and+
